                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Confirmed my long-standing suspicions about color cloud by reviewing my log file.  Contrary to spell listing in lucy (source is spdat file?), the duration is not 8 seconds.  At least, it isn't 8 seconds on the client side to be sure.
<br />

<br />
Example one:
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:31 2004] You begin casting Color Cloud.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:33 2004] Foul Pusling is stunned by scintillating colors.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:33 2004] Corrupted Pusling is stunned by scintillating colors.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:38 2004] You begin casting Sleep.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Corrupted Pusling hits a scrounging rat for 513 points of damage.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Corrupted Pusling hits a scrounging rat for 174 points of damage.
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Foul Pusling tries to hit YOU, but YOUR magical skin absorbs the blow!
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Foul Pusling tries to hit YOU, but YOUR magical skin absorbs the blow!
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Foul Pusling tries to hit YOU, but misses!
<br />
[Fri May 28 21:36:40 2004] Your spell is interrupted.
<br />

<br />
Duration = 7 seconds (2 targets)
<br />

<br />
Example two:
<br />
[Fri May 28 23:13:10 2004] You begin casting Color Cloud.
<br />
[Fri May 28 23:13:12 2004] Foul Pusling is stunned by scintillating colors.
<br />
 [Fri May 28 23:13:19 2004] Foul Pusling hits Pukrup for 239 points of damage.
<br />

<br />
Duration = 7 seconds
<br />

<br />
Example 3:
<br />
[Sat May 29 01:49:10 2004] You begin casting Color Cloud.
<br />
[Sat May 29 01:49:12 2004] A doomed Yunta witchdoctor is stunned by scintillating colors.
<br />
[Sat May 29 01:49:19 2004] A doomed Yunta witchdoctor hits Eandayen for 372 points of damage.
<br />

<br />
Duration = 7 seconds
<br />

<br />
Example 4:
<br />
[Sun May 30 18:10:16 2004] You begin casting Color Cloud.
<br />
[Sun May 30 18:10:19 2004] Enslaved Mystic pet is stunned by scintillating colors.
<br />
[Sun May 30 18:10:25 2004] Enslaved Mystic pet tries to bite YOU, but YOUR magical skin absorbs the blow!
<br />

<br />
Duration = 6 seconds
<br />

<br />
I searched and searched and searched but was unable to find an instance of an 8 second duration.  What does this mean?  It means the spell is a bad bet to use in recharm scenarios for one thing.
<br />

<br />
Command of Druzil has a base cast time of 5.0 seconds.  Add a common spell haste item (Spell Haste IV or Haste of Solusek) and you are at 4.25 seconds.  Add Blessing of Reverence (10 pct stacking spell haste) and you are down to 3.75 seconds.
<br />

<br />
The standard spell gem refresh time is 2.25 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Therefore with common haste items alone, your recast time is 6.5 seconds.  6 seconds with BoR.  Since our logs do not show fractions of seconds, your guess is as good as mine what happens to those.
<br />

<br />
With Color Cloud stunning for between 6 and 7 seconds as shown above, casting this spell is not a reliable method to recharm.  We all know what happens if we hit a spell gem too early on refresh (spell recovery time not met).  With any pause at all before recasting CoD after a color cloud stun, all we've done is blow 350 mana.  Better to suck it up and try to channel.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nokei Orhaste &lt;Retired&gt; E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10</a></span>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?24364" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mirabelle - Foresaken Rogue - Mal`Ganis</a>
<br />
<a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?33981" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lucies - Priest alt</a>
<br />

