                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I read here some time ago about a great trick with Color Cloud.  When my pet break, I immediately Tash then CC.  Then I run away while the spells are grey out, but keep the pet in casting sight.  I stop, do a small turn and cast CoD.  MOB will become free from CC before he is charmed but will not get near.  Do it a few times and you will get a feel for how far to run, how long it takes for spells to "ungrey," etc.  This, of course, is for unsnared mobs.  If its snared, you don't need any of this crap.
<br />

<br />
However, I do plan to to MM after I finish some defensive AAs (I am still a noob/casual/whatever, k).  12 seconds sounds like eternity.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />

<br />
Shurik</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Shurik
