                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just wanted to add my 2 cp to what is going on with stun. This is only my experience and my hypothesis for it, but I think it's a good hunch. I use our regular stuns alot (pre-color cloud) in Nurga. I DC a little sneak and stun stun stun stun stun stun stun stun stun stun....well, you get the picture....As long as I keep him stunned, the mob never touches me (unless I get a resist) and the stuns last full duration. Notice though I said I charm a sneak (a rogue mob) These guys only pierce...
<br />

<br />
Ok, a slightly different twist on the same scenario as above. While chain stunning, I decide to whack the gob with my snake stick. When I do manage to land a hit, this 1H Blunt to their little green skulls seems to end my stun. Little gob acttually gets a few swings in and can whack ME good. Perhaps that 1H blunt stun is 'overwriting' the first stun...
<br />

<br />
Now, add some guildies into the mix. Particular guildies that like to bash the mobs I'm stunning. If they bash the mob, my stun doesn't last full duration, and the mob will actually have a chance to get a few swings in. And I asked my guildies if they were bashing and they were....when they stopped bashing, we didn't have this problem. In the first example the mob never had a chance to take a swing. 
<br />

<br />
So, in conclusion, I believe that any mobs or PCs that are bashing or somehow stunning the mobs that you are using Color Cloud on, they are interrupting your stun (8 sec) and replacing it with their shorter duration stun. Thus resulting in what appears to be shorter stun. Not sure if this is a bug, or how stuns should work. Just what I think is happening.
<br />

<br />
Fading Illusion</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
