                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I haven't used WoM in a long time : /  Just sticking to color cloud, even with MM long in the dust.  The extended duration of WoM would be appreciated, but I think there are too many things that can go wrong whilst a mob is mezzed.  First off, dots.  We try to avoid these like the plague, but hey, it happens.  Second, the pet is very vulnerable to being hit from other things.  AEs, careless melee, etc etc.  It <span style="font-weight: bold">shouldn't</span> happen, but it does.  With a stun, the mob can't be "broken" early, and if there's another mob that your group is on, if you're in range, the stun's helping them out, too, instead of just a quick mez that gets broken with no benefit.  I've got spell haste iv and do just fine on recharming.  In the words of the immortal Mr. T, I pity the fool that doesn't back up after stunning/WoMing.  If you can't cast spells anyway, better to give yourself some space.  I rarely have issues with recharming.  The only thing that catches me every once in awhile is when I'm sped and don't come to a complete stop before recasting CoD : /  Is there anyone else out there that would use color cloud over WoM, or am I a talentless stooge putting myself and others at too much risk?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
