                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've used it on plenty of mobs that are above the color stun cap(55) and its worked on all of them.  If something hits the mob or the mob is dotted/nuked/stunned  it breaks immediately.  
<br />

<br />
It's not real useful as a means of interrupting casting on a healing/gating mob because it is broken almost immediately by a melee before it has a chance to interrupt.  
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure I've tried it on any mob above level 60 though so maybe it isn't useful there.  I haven't used it in awhile because a mez will interrupt a gate/heal if the mob is mezzable and I haven't been fighitng things I can't mez lately <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I'm really new at charming so just trying to find ways to reduce the mana usage of the technique <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

